uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.jdbc.filter

Class BaseCombineFilter<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.jdbc.filter.FilterSet<T>
      • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.jdbc.filter.BaseCombineFilter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of target
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    BaseFilter<T>, BaseSQLFilter<T>, BinaryFilter<T>, JoinFilter<T>, OrderFilter<T>, PatternFilter<T>, Targetted<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AndFilter, BaseSQLCombineFilter

    public abstract class BaseCombineFilter<T>
extends FilterSet<T>
implements PatternFilter<T>, JoinFilter<T>, OrderFilter<T>, BinaryFilter<T>
    Base class for Filters than combines multiple SQL filters. Only the SQL parts of the filters are considered by this class. This class assumes it is ok to supress multiple copies of equal filters.
    Author:
    spb
